        "Text": {
          "type": "cexolocstring",
          "value": {
            "0": "OK, so, now you're dead.  The only thing you'll notice right away is that whatever clothes you were wearing have turned gray.  Also, you know have a token called \"Wraith\" and some others.  You are now in the Shadowlands, that mystical place right up against the Real World (also known as the Skinlands) and the final destinations of souls everywhere, wherever those places may be.  When you are here, interacting with other Wraiths is remarkably similar to existing in the Real World.  I haven't even bothered to design much to the Shadowlands, letting each GM design it on their own.  Classically, it would be have a capitol city (Stygia), perhaps some rivers, different factions, guards to enforce the law of the land, and the wastelands would be patrolled by insane spirits called Spectres.  "
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "__struct_id": 1,
        "Animation": {
          "type": "dword",
          "value": 0
        },
        "AnimLoop": {
