              "IsChild": {
                "type": "byte",
                "value": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "Script": {
          "type": "resref",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Sound": {
          "type": "resref",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Speaker": {
          "type": "cexostring",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Text": {
          "type": "cexolocstring",
          "value": {
            "0": "All these powers are fueled by Pathos.  Pathos is essentially energy taken from the living.  In some cases, it is represented by people remembering the dead.  In other cases, it is taken from people's dreams.  You can gain Pathos either by being in a graveyard at midnight (which is when people remembering you manifests itself) or by being near a person while they sleep.  In game terms, you use it while people are resting nearby.  It interrupts their rest (with nightmares) but you gain a point of Pathos.  You have a potion for this you just have to drink when you are nearby a PC resting.  "
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "__struct_id": 6,
        "Animation": {
          "type": "dword",
