        },
        "Sound": {
          "type": "resref",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Speaker": {
          "type": "cexostring",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Text": {
          "type": "cexolocstring",
          "value": {
            "0": "Many of your powers will work in the Shadowlands, but rarely serve a point.  The biggest advantage you have in being a Wraith is the ability to spy on other PCs without them knowing you are there.  You can also use Poltergeist powers to change the tides of battles, influence the living, protect your haunt, etc.  Also in game terms, you can technically attack people.  However, as a Wraith, you start with a -25 to hit, so there isn't much of a point to it.  Once you start a combat with an NPC, just so you know, they will continue to fight with you until you leave the Skinlands, even though the odds are good that they can't hurt you either.  "
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "__struct_id": 8,
        "Animation": {
          "type": "dword",
          "value": 0
        },
        "AnimLoop": {
          "type": "byte",
          "value": 1
