        },
        "RepliesList": {
          "type": "list",
          "value": [
            {
              "__struct_id": 0,
              "Active": {
                "type": "resref",
                "value": ""
              },
              "Index": {
                "type": "dword",
                "value": 8
              },
              "IsChild": {
                "type": "byte",
                "value": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "Script": {
          "type": "resref",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Sound": {
          "type": "resref",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Speaker": {
          "type": "cexostring",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Text": {
          "type": "cexolocstring",
          "value": {
            "0": "The biggest bane to a Wraith is a spell called Bind.  If anyone (PC or NPC) uses it near you, it will teleport you to them, and paralyze you there, trapped.  For role-playing purposes, this would be to force you into bargains, or drain your Pathos for other purposes, etc.  "
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "__struct_id": 9,
        "Animation": {
          "type": "dword",
          "value": 0
        },
        "AnimLoop": {
          "type": "byte",
          "value": 1
        },
        "Comment": {
          "type": "cexostring",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Delay": {
          "type": "dword",
          "value": 4294967295
        },
        "Quest": {
          "type": "cexostring",
          "value": ""
        },
        "RepliesList": {
          "type": "list",
          "value": []
        },
        "Script": {
          "type": "resref",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Sound": {
          "type": "resref",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Speaker": {
          "type": "cexostring",
          "value": ""
        },
        "Text": {
          "type": "cexolocstring",
          "value": {
            "0": "It also goes without saying that as a Wraith you cannot sleep (i.e. Rest).  Any powers relying on that from your life are useless now, unless you can Manifest well enough to do Life From Death, which allows you to basically be human throughout the night.  If you were a ghoul, vampire, werecreature, or zombie, any powers from those forms are gone now too.  The only exception is the Lycanthrope power Step Sideways.  Step Sideways allows werecreatures to enter the Spirit World (a place filled with benevolent spirits, not the souls of dead people).  If you were a Lycanthrope with Step Sideways, you can now travel back and forth freely between the ShadowLands and the Spirit World.  "
          }
        }
      }
